<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Hungary-Sex     08-03 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Hungary-Sex,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hungary Experiments with Sex Magazine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communist Hungary will soon publish
``Sexpress,'' its first sex magazine, with British pop star
Samantha Fox on the cover of the first issue, the official MTI news
agency reported.
   The 80-page publication, to sell for about $2.20, will be
published jointly by High Society GMBH of West Germany, the
Nepszava publishing house in Budapest and the National Health
Protection Council, MTI said Tuesday.
   It will cover issues of sexual culture, health, sports and
physical fitness, the report said.
   ``The magazine's price is rather high by Hungarian standards.
Nevertheless, the first 100,000 copies are expected to sell out
quickly,'' MTI said.
   Three more issues are planned to come out this year, the report
said.
   The Hungarian publishers say they plan to donate part of their
expected 20 percent profit to ``AIDS research and publicit on how
to prevent the spread of the disease,'' in Hungary, MTI said.
</TEXT>
