<HEAD>Safety Agency Issues Dishwasher Warning</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Consumer Product Safety Commission is
warning that modifications are needed on approximately 75,000
Whirlpool undercounter dishwashers that could catch fire.
   Whirlpool Corp. of Benton Harbor, Mich., is offering to replace
the potentially faulty selector switch on the dishwashers, the
commission said Tuesday. Involved are Whirlpool undercounter
dishwasher models DU7400XS-0, DU7600XS-0, DU7800XS-0, DU900XR-0 and
DU900XR-1.
   Whirlpool is asking owners of the washers to telephone the
company at 1-800-541-5746 to arrange for the free repairs.
Consumers can check the model number on a plate found on the right
front edge of the tub after the door is opened.
   Safety officials urged owners not to use the washers until the
repairs are completed. Consumers needing more information can
contact the safety commission at 1-800-638-2772.
