<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-LadyBing     08-03 0278</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Lady Bing,0286</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lady Bing Hospitalized in Psychiatric Ward</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lady Carroll Douglass Bing, the wife of former
Metropolitan Opera impresario Sir Rudolf Bing, has been
hospitalized and undergoing psychiatric treatment for the past two
weeks, her attorney says.
   ``She's an emotionally fragile lady,'' her attorney, Harvey
Sladkus said Tueday. He blamed her current instability on attempts
by Bing's attorneys to annul her marriage.
   Sladkus said the 48-year-old Lady Bing remains at St. Luke's
Hospital, where she was taken by police after a July 17 incident.
Sladkus said he did not know the nature of the incident.
   The Bings were married in January 1987 in Maclean, Va. Bing's
attorneys are attempting to have the marriage annulled on the
grounds that the 86-year-old former impresario did not know what he
was doing when he married his wife. Bing has Alzheimer's disease.
   On May 9, state Supreme Court Justice Carmen Ciparick ordered a
psychiatric examination of Lady Bing at her attorney's request.
Lady Bing had shown an apparent inability to follow the court's
directions.
   ``My client has lost touch with reality,'' Sladkus told the
judge.
   That same day the judge ordered Lady Bing to leave her husband's
apartment for six hours each day so that nurses could attend to him.
   Sladkus said he has asked the judge to stay all annulment
proceedings until doctors say Lady Bing is able to defend herself.
He said the judge scheduled Aug. 10 for further proceedings in the
case.
   Sladkus said he was told of Lady Bing's hospitalization by her
sister, who lives in Washington, D.C.
   The attorney said he did not know how long his client would
remain hospitalized.
</TEXT>
