<HEAD>George Bush Wins!</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George Bush, the $3 million Lotto winner, says
like his namesake, the vice president, he is a fiscal conservative.
   ``I'll put the first few checks in the bank,'' said Bush, 47, a
mortgage banker from Connecticut who won the money in last week's
New York Lotto.
   ``I don't plan to change my life,'' he said Tuesday after
meeting the press at the Lotto offices.
   Bush shares the $6 million prize with Martin Ahern, 57, of New
York. They will each get $142,857 a year for 20 years.
   ``I was pretty positive I was going to win Lotto,'' Bush said.
``You just get that winning feeling.''
