<2ND_LINE>PM-Silva Killed,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Manslaughter, Drunken Driving Charges Filed Against Man in Actor's
Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WHITTIER, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Manslaughter and drunken driving charges
have been filed against a man in the weekend crash that killed
former ``Hill Street Blues'' actor Trinidad Silva Jr.
   Douglas Robert Owens, 35, of La Habra, was charged with felony
vehicular manslaughter, felony hit-and-run driving and two felony
counts of driving under the influence of alcohol, Deputy District
Attorney Dinko Bozanich said Tuesday.
   Owens faces up to 12 years in prison if convicted on all counts.
   He has been jailed on $5,000 bail since the crash Sunday.
   Police said Owens' car ran a light and broadsided Silva's pickup
truck. The 38-year-old actor, who wasn't wearing a seatbelt, was
hurled through the windshield and died of head injuries.
   Silva played the wisecracking gang leader Jesus Martinez in the
NBC series ``Hill Street Blues.'' He won critical praise for his
portrayal of an aging gang member in the movie ``Colors'' earlier
this year.
   Silva's 2-year-old son, Samuel, and wife, Sofia, 28, suffered
minor injuries in the accident.
