<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Train Suicide,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Kills 3, Then Kills Self By Standing In Front of Train</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LODI, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man killed three people by ramming their
car with his pickup truck then took his own life by standing naked
in front of a speeding train, the coroner said.
   The train was traveling 60 mph Tuesday when it struck
42-year-old Michael E. Nelson, scattering body parts up to 150
yards away, said San Joaquin County Deputy Coroner Gerald Krein.
   Nelson had hit a parked car from behind, and both cars burst
into flames, Krein said. The bodies in the car were burned beyond
recognition, according to the California Highway Patrol.
   Nelson got out of his truck, stripped and walked 100 yards into
the path of the train, said Krein.
</TEXT>
