   July 31
   Press-Telegram, Long Beach, Calif., on the McKay report on Meese:
   Ed Meese and his lawyers say independent counsel James McKay was
unfair to Meese. Having decided not to prosecute him, McKay then
issued a report saying he's convinced that Meese broke the law and
that a jury would find him guilty. ...
   It was unfair to Meese. It was also unfair to the people of the
United States. ...
   But McKay never tested in court his conclusion that jurors would
find the attorney general guilty as charged. ...
   McKay decided not to prosecute on the ground that he lacked
evidence that Meese did what he did for personal gain. But Meese
realized personal gain from what he did. ...
   Meese says McKay's report vindicates him. That's foolish. What
McKay's report does is cover Meese with mud. ...
   The only way Meese can get all the mud off now is to demand that
the Justice Department finish McKay's job and prosecute. Then a
jury can vindicate Meese. Or it can do what McKay said it would.
   Either way, the unfairness that stains the Meese report will be
removed.
