<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--ChemicalWeapons     08-03 0114</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Chemical Weapons,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Army Distributes Anti-Chemical Weapon Pill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Israeli army has supplied its soldiers with
a new pill that increases their immunity to chemical weapons, the
military's chief physician said Wednesday.
   The military has in the past year developed a formula that
boosts the body's immune reaction to such chemicals, said Brig.
Gen. Yehuda Danon.
   The military has also conducted experiments in hospitals with
medical teams trained to treat victims of chemical warfare, the
daily newspaper Maariv reported.
   A report by Tel Aviv University's Jaffee Center for Strategic
Studies says Arab countries possess chemical weapons that
constitute ``a threat against Israel ... (that) can only grow in
the future.''
</TEXT>
