<HEAD>Archeologists To Search For Human Remains From Volcano</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Archaeologists will search for the
remains of about 35,000 people killed more than a century ago when
the Krakatau volcano erupted in West Java, a report said Wednesday.
   Archaeologist Halwany Michrab said his team would dig in coastal
Banten district, about 125 miles west of Jakarta, where the volcano
erupted in 1883.
   The skull of a person who is believed to have been killed by the
eruption was found recently in Banten.
   Michrab told the newspaper Suara Pembaruan that any remains
recovered would be donated to a museum.
