<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--WomenOnly     08-03 0177</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Women Only,0181</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Men Allowed to Join Women's Spa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Women Only spa won't be so any more under
a settlement reached in a sex discrimination lawsuit against the
health club.
   Men must give 24 hours notice before using the spa until
membership is at least 10 percent male, attorney Gloria Allred said
Tuesday.
   ``I think it should be made clear to everyone and every business
that wholesale discrimination against any group ... is going to
lead to failure,'' said Anthony Flacco of North Hollywood, who
brought the lawsuit.
   The spa agreed to give Flacco, 38, a free one-year membership
and pay $15,000 in attorney's fees as part of a settlement, said
Ms. Allred, who represented Flacco.
   The settlement ``does not represent a change in Women's Only
commitment to provide a non-threatening private atmosphere for our
10,000 women members to meet their special exercise needs,'' said
Barbara E. Roberts, attorney for the spa.
   Flacco said he wanted to join Women Only's San Fernando Valley
spa because the club he attended was overcrowded.
</TEXT>
