at the Feminist Women's Health Center. When the activists refused
to leave, police arrested them. Another 20 abortion opponents who
arrived later carried picket signs and unfurled banners.
   Atlanta authorities have said the protesters will remain in jail
without bond unless they agree to identify themselves. Only a few
have done so during the court hearings held for them so far.
