<FILEID>AP-NR-08-03-88 0930EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f PM-GoodyearRestructure     08-03 0212</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Goodyear Restructure,0221</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Goodyear Announces Company Will Divide Into Two Divisions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co. will realign its
businesses into two divisions, tires and general products, the
company has announced.
   The restructuring announcement came after the close of the stock
market Tuesday. In trading on the New York Stock Exchange, Goodyear
fell 25 cents a share to close at $61.87{.
   In addition to making tires, Goodyear manufactures a variety of
rubber, chemical and plastic products.
   Chairman Robert E. Mercer said the reorganization will
streamline the company to be more flexible and responsive to the
changing marketplace.
   ``These two divisions will operate with a high degree of
autonomy and have their own manufacturing, development, financial
staff, materials management and other support functions,'' Mercer
said. ``We're in a position to take further steps to remove layers
of management and reduce overhead.''
   The global tire division will be directed by Jacques Sardas and
the general products division by Hoyt Wells. Each will have the
titles of president and chief operating officer of his division.
   Under the restructuring, manufacturing operations have been
consolidated in the tire and general products operations to create
totally integrated business units, the announcement said.
   Goodyear earned $440 million on sales of $9.9 billion in 1987.
</TEXT>
